records.addlTxt:
1:55 PM Defendant Kenneth J Knotek in court, in custody.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Kenneth J Knotek.  Prosecuting attorney Abbey Nickolie in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Case 22MC1792 is dismissed and read in to this matter.
Recommendations by the State.  Recommendations by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.


The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
12 Months.  First 6 Months Straight Time.  Remainder of sentence may be served with Huber with RELEASE FOR WORK, WORK SEARCH AND TREATMENT.  

Term of Probation: 18 Months
Conditions of Probation:
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; 
-	Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	Follow through with the ARC program;
-	Follow through with other programs offering assistance;
-	Maintain/Obtain employment/volunteer work or other activity within 30 days of release;
-	Work on obtaining a valid Driver's License;
-	Become involved with AA and maintain contact with sponsor;
-	Work with St. Vincent De Paul with assistance living in the community;
-	No new law violations;

Condition Time: 30 Days Jail.  Credit for 24 days to be applied to the Condition Time.

COSTS:  $ 243.00

DV Surcharge: $ 100.00

DNA Surcharge: $ 200.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation within the first 10 months of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.  As an alternative to payment the defendant may complete community service as approved by the Agent.  Each hour of community service to equal $25.00 towards financial obligations.
